init_text:
Once upon a time there was an old mother pig who had one hundred little pigs and not enough food to feed them. So when they were old enough, she sent them out into the world to seek their fortunes. You know the story about the first three little pigs. This is a story about the 92nd little pig.

The 92nd little pig built a house out of depleted uranium. And the wolf was like, "dude."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf found the house of depleted uranium and was like, "this is hard to bite."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: But the wolf decided to try.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So he blew and blew, and blew and blew as hard as he could, but the house of depleted uranium didn't fall down.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I guess I'll just have to come back tomorrow and try again," said the wolf.

actions.text: But then the wolf thought of something.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Hey, I know another way to get into this house," he said.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So the wolf came back that night when the Pig was asleep.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He came through the chimney, and he snuck over to the Pig's bedroom.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And he looked at the Pig sleeping, and he had an idea.

actions.text: "This Pig is one smart fellow," thought the Wolf.
